{
  "texts": [
    "The AUC of the ROC and of the PR curves are computed to quantify the ability of a model to classify sequences.",
    "For ROC curves, the AUC is equal to one when the classification is perfect.",
    "It is equal to 0.5 when the model performs as poorly as a classifier that is randomly sampling from a uniform distribution.",
    "For PR curves, the AUC is also equal to one when the classification is perfect, while it is equal to the ratio of positive entries over the total number of entries in the datasets when the classification is random.",
    "The amino acid reconstruction accuracy."
  ]
}